01128         number_to_move = (int) ((yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr)) - 1;
01129 
01130         for ( i = 0; i < number_to_move; ++i )
01131                 *(dest++) = *(source++);
01132 
01133         if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buffer_status == YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING )
01134                 /* don't do the read, it's not guaranteed to return an EOF,
01135                  * just force an EOF
01136                  */
01137                 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars) = 0;
01138 
01139         else
01140                 {
01141                         int num_to_read =
01142                         YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size - number_to_move - 1;
01143 
01144                 while ( num_to_read <= 0 )
01145                         { /* Not enough room in the buffer - grow it. */
01146 
01147                         /* just a shorter name for the current buffer */
01148                         YY_BUFFER_STATE b = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER;
01149 
01150                         int yy_c_buf_p_offset =
01151                                 (int) ((yy_c_buf_p) - b->yy_ch_buf);
01152 
01153                         if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
01154                                 {
01155                                 int new_size = b->yy_buf_size * 2;
01156 
01157                                 if ( new_size <= 0 )
01158                                         b->yy_buf_size += b->yy_buf_size / 8;
01159                                 else
01160                                         b->yy_buf_size *= 2;
01161 
01162                                 b->yy_ch_buf = (char *)
01163                                         /* Include room in for 2 EOB chars. */
01164                                         yyrealloc((void *) b->yy_ch_buf,b->yy_buf_size + 2  );
01165                                 }
01166                         else
01167                                 /* Can't grow it, we don't own it. */
01168                                 b->yy_ch_buf = 0;
01169 
01170                         if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
01171                                 YY_FATAL_ERROR(
01172                                 "fatal error - scanner input buffer overflow" );
01173 
01174                         (yy_c_buf_p) = &b->yy_ch_buf[yy_c_buf_p_offset];
01175 
01176                         num_to_read = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size -
01177                                                 number_to_move - 1;
01178 
01179                         }
01180 
01181                 if ( num_to_read > YY_READ_BUF_SIZE )
01182                         num_to_read = YY_READ_BUF_SIZE;
01183 
01184                 /* Read in more data. */
01185                 YY_INPUT( (&YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[number_to_move]),
01186                         (yy_n_chars), (size_t) num_to_read );
01187 
01188                 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
01189                 }
01190 
01191         if ( (yy_n_chars) == 0 )
01192                 {
01193                 if ( number_to_move == YY_MORE_ADJ )
01194                         {
01195                         ret_val = EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
01196                         yyrestart(yyin  );
01197                         }
01198 
01199                 else
01200                         {
01201                         ret_val = EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
01202                         YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buffer_status =
01203                                 YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING;
01204                         }
01205                 }
01206 
01207         else
01208                 ret_val = EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN;
01209 
01210         if ((yy_size_t) ((yy_n_chars) + number_to_move) > YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size) {
01211                 /* Extend the array by 50%, plus the number we really need. */
01212                 yy_size_t new_size = (yy_n_chars) + number_to_move + ((yy_n_chars) >> 1);
01213                 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf = (char *) yyrealloc((void *) YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf,new_size  );
01214                 if ( ! YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf )
01215                         YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_get_next_buffer()" );
01216         }
01217 
01218         (yy_n_chars) += number_to_move;
01219         YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars)] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
01220         YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars) + 1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
01221 
01222         (yytext_ptr) = &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[0];
01223 
01224         return ret_val;
01225 }

01284     static void yyunput (int c, register char * yy_bp )
01285 {
01286         register char *yy_cp;
01287     
01288     yy_cp = (yy_c_buf_p);
01289 
01290         /* undo effects of setting up yytext */
01291         *yy_cp = (yy_hold_char);
01292 
01293         if ( yy_cp < YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf + 2 )
01294                 { /* need to shift things up to make room */
01295                 /* +2 for EOB chars. */
01296                 register int number_to_move = (yy_n_chars) + 2;
01297                 register char *dest = &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[
01298                                         YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size + 2];
01299                 register char *source =
01300                                 &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[number_to_move];
01301 
01302                 while ( source > YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf )
01303                         *--dest = *--source;
01304 
01305                 yy_cp += (int) (dest - source);
01306                 yy_bp += (int) (dest - source);
01307                 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars =
01308                         (yy_n_chars) = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size;
01309 
01310                 if ( yy_cp < YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf + 2 )
01311                         YY_FATAL_ERROR( "flex scanner push-back overflow" );
01312                 }
01313 
01314         *--yy_cp = (char) c;
01315 
01316         (yytext_ptr) = yy_bp;
01317         (yy_hold_char) = *yy_cp;
01318         (yy_c_buf_p) = yy_cp;
01319 }

01321 #ifndef YY_NO_INPUT
01322 #ifdef __cplusplus
01323     static int yyinput (void)
01324 #else

01326 #endif

01328 {
01329         int c;
01330     
01331         *(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
01332 
01333         if ( *(yy_c_buf_p) == YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
01334                 {
01335                 /* yy_c_buf_p now points to the character we want to return.
01336                  * If this occurs *before* the EOB characters, then it's a
01337                  * valid NUL; if not, then we've hit the end of the buffer.
01338                  */

01413 /** Switch to a different input buffer.
01414  * @param new_buffer The new input buffer.
01415  * 
01416  */
01417     void yy_switch_to_buffer  (YY_BUFFER_STATE  new_buffer )
01418 {
01419     
01420         /* TODO. We should be able to replace this entire function body
01421          * with
01422          *              yypop_buffer_state();

01537 /** Discard all buffered characters. On the next scan, YY_INPUT will be called.
01538  * @param b the buffer state to be flushed, usually @c YY_CURRENT_BUFFER.
01539  * 
01540  */
01541     void yy_flush_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE  b )
01542 {
01543         if ( ! b )
01544                 return;
01545 
01546         b->yy_n_chars = 0;
01547

01566  *  if necessary.

01569  */
01570 void yypush_buffer_state (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer )
01571 {
01572         if (new_buffer == NULL)
01573                 return;
01574 
01575         yyensure_buffer_stack();
01576 
01577         /* This block is copied from yy_switch_to_buffer. */
01578         if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
01579                 {

01597  *  The next element becomes the new top.

01616 /* Allocates the stack if it does not exist.
01617  *  Guarantees space for at least one push.
01618  */
01619 static void yyensure_buffer_stack (void)
01620 {
01621         int num_to_alloc;
01622     
01623         if (!(yy_buffer_stack)) {
01624 
01625                 /* First allocation is just for 2 elements, since we don't know if this
01626                  * scanner will even need a stack. We use 2 instead of 1 to avoid an
01627                  * immediate realloc on the next call.
01628          */
01629                 num_to_alloc = 1;
01630                 (yy_buffer_stack) = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyalloc
01631                                                                 (num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
01632                                                                 );
01633                 if ( ! (yy_buffer_stack) )
01634                         YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyensure_buffer_stack()" );
01635                                                                   
01636                 memset((yy_buffer_stack), 0, num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
01637                                 
01638                 (yy_buffer_stack_max) = num_to_alloc;
01639                 (yy_buffer_stack_top) = 0;
01640                 return;
01641         }
01642 
01643         if ((yy_buffer_stack_top) >= ((yy_buffer_stack_max)) - 1){
01644 
01645                 /* Increase the buffer to prepare for a possible push. */
01646                 int grow_size = 8 /* arbitrary grow size */;
01647 
01648                 num_to_alloc = (yy_buffer_stack_max) + grow_size;
01649                 (yy_buffer_stack) = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyrealloc
01650                                                                 ((yy_buffer_stack),
01651                                                                 num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
01652                                                                 );
01653                 if ( ! (yy_buffer_stack) )
01654                         YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyensure_buffer_stack()" );
01655 
01656                 /* zero only the new slots.*/
01657                 memset((yy_buffer_stack) + (yy_buffer_stack_max), 0, grow_size * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
01658                 (yy_buffer_stack_max) = num_to_alloc;
01659         }
01660 }

01662 /** Setup the input buffer state to scan directly from a user-specified character buffer.
01663  * @param base the character buffer
01664  * @param size the size in bytes of the character buffer

01680                 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_scan_buffer()" );

01883 /* yylex_destroy is for both reentrant and non-reentrant scanners. */
01884 int yylex_destroy  (void)
01885 {
01886     
01887     /* Pop the buffer stack, destroying each element. */
01888         while(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
01889                 yy_delete_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER  );
01890                 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = NULL;
01891                 yypop_buffer_state();
01892         }
01893 
01894         /* Destroy the stack itself. */
01895         yyfree((yy_buffer_stack) );
01896         (yy_buffer_stack) = NULL;
01897 
01898     /* Reset the globals. This is important in a non-reentrant scanner so the next time
01899      * yylex() is called, initialization will occur. */
01900     yy_init_globals( );

01902     return 0;
